# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit a real .env.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Postgres connection. For local Docker Compose the app service overrides this
# to point at the `db` container; for running `prisma migrate`/`dev` on the host
# against the compose DB, use localhost:
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://estate:estate@localhost:5432/estate?schema=public"

# Auth.js session signing secret (REQUIRED). Generate one with:
#   npx auth secret       (writes AUTH_SECRET for you)
# or: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET="replace-me-with-a-long-random-string"

# Field-level encryption key for sensitive data at rest (REQUIRED).
# Must be base64 of exactly 32 bytes. Generate with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
ENCRYPTION_KEY="replace-me-base64-32-bytes"

# Claude API — powers the conversational explanation layer ONLY.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."
# Optional model override (defaults to claude-opus-4-8):
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL="claude-opus-4-8"

# Plaid (OPTIONAL). If unset, the app uses a built-in MOCK adapter so account
# linking works without credentials. Add these to use the live sandbox:
# PLAID_CLIENT_ID=""
# PLAID_SECRET=""
# PLAID_ENV="sandbox"

# Market data (OPTIONAL) — powers the informational "Market Snapshot" widget on
# the dashboard (general index info only; NOT tied to your accounts and NOT
# investment advice). Free Finnhub API key: https://finnhub.io. If unset, the
# widget shows "Market data unavailable" and nothing else is affected.
MARKET_DATA_API_KEY=""

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Billing / Stripe (OPTIONAL until you turn on paid plans).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The app ships with a working FREE tier and full server-side tier gating. The
# subscription TIER is read from the database (the Subscription row), which is
# the single source of truth — NOT from Stripe directly. When these vars are
# unset, /api/billing/* returns 503 "billing_not_configured" and the pricing
# page shows a "checkout isn't live yet" notice; everything else works.
#
# Set up: create 4 recurring Prices in the Stripe Dashboard (Plus + Pro, each
# monthly and annual) and paste their price IDs below. The webhook secret comes
# from `stripe listen` (local) or the Dashboard webhook endpoint (deployed).
#   Never store raw card data — Stripe Checkout + the Billing Portal handle it.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_..."
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET="whsec_..."
# STRIPE_PLUS_MONTHLY_PRICE_ID="price_..."
# STRIPE_PLUS_ANNUAL_PRICE_ID="price_..."
# STRIPE_PRO_MONTHLY_PRICE_ID="price_..."
# STRIPE_PRO_ANNUAL_PRICE_ID="price_..."

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Email (OPTIONAL) — transactional email for the waitlist confirmation link.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# No provider is wired up yet: the app uses a MOCK adapter that LOGS the email
# (including the confirmation URL) to the server console instead of sending it.
# That is enough to test the waitlist end-to-end locally. To send real email,
# pick a provider, implement its branch in src/lib/email/send.ts, and add its
# key here (e.g. RESEND_API_KEY). Keep the mock fallback so the app still runs
# without credentials.
# RESEND_API_KEY=""
